@layout DefaultLayout
@page "/portfolio/raidhealersimulator"
@{
    var openGraphModel = new OpenGraphModel()
    {
        Title = "Raid Healer Simulator - Fydar",
        Description = "The simulation experience of what it’s like to be a healer in an MMORPG raid, complete with a variety of abilities and a challenging boss battle.",
        CanonicalUrl = "https://fydar.dev/portfolio/raidhealersimulator",
        Properties = [
            new OpenGraphModelImage()
            {
                Url = "https://fydar.dev/media/raidhealersimulator/social.webp",
                Alt = "Promotional material for the game 'Raid Healer Simulator'."
            }
        ]
    };
    var linkData = new LinkData()
    {
        new LinkDataBreadcrumbList()
        {
            new LinkDataBreadcrumbListItem()
            {
                Name = "Portfolio",
                Item = "https://fydar.dev/portfolio"
            },
            new LinkDataBreadcrumbListItem()
            {
                Name = "Raid Healer Simulator",
                Item = "https://fydar.dev/portfolio/raidhealersimulator"
            }
        }
    };
}

<HeadContent>
    <OpenGraphComponent Model="@openGraphModel" />
    <LinkDataComponent Model="@linkData" />
</HeadContent>

<article class="page-raidhealersimulator">

    <div class="fullscreen" data-nosnippet>
        <div class="parallax-frame parallax-focalanchortop" style="--animation-time: 0.5;">
            <picture class="parallax-layer" style="--parallax-multiplier: 0.5; background-color: #17181c;">
                <img decoding="async" src="@Assets["media/raidhealersimulator/background.webp"]" style="top: 52px; height: calc(100% - 56px); object-position: left;" />
            </picture>
        </div>

        <div class="fullscreen-footer">
            <div class="container">
                <picture>
                    <img decoding="async" class="titlecard" src="@Assets["media/raidhealersimulator/titlecard.svg"]" alt="Title card for the game 'Raid Healer Simulator'." />
                </picture>

                <div class="titlerow">
                    <div class="flexible-space"></div>
                    <SteamPlayButton href="/play/raidhealersimulator">Play in Browser</SteamPlayButton>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cascade-container">
            <div class="cascade" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, #00ffcc1a 0%, #7f893230 75%, #3d270c47 100%), url(media/noise.svg);">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <Block_ArticleHeader>
            <h1 data-nosnippet>Raid Healer Simulator</h1>
        </Block_ArticleHeader>

        <Block_ArticleIntroduction>
            <Sidebar>
                <img decoding="async" class="article-featuredimage" src="@Assets["media/raidhealersimulator/social.webp"]" alt="Promotional material for the game 'Raid Healer Simulator'." />

                <Block_PillCloud>
                    <Pill_GameJam />
                    <Pill_Unity />
                    <Pill_CSharp />
                </Block_PillCloud>

                <p>@openGraphModel.Description.Default</p>

                <menu class="externallinks" aria-label="Project External links">
                    <li><a href="https://github.com/fydar/RaidHealerSimulator" target="_blank"><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-github" Alt="GitHub" /></a></li>
                    <li class="palette-youtube"><a href="https://youtu.be/wZhdUXI0Wyg" target="_blank"><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-youtube" Alt="YouTube" /></a></li>
                </menu>

                <ShareLink Url="@openGraphModel.CanonicalUrl.Html" />
            </Sidebar>
            <Container>
                <EmbedYouTube Url="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/wZhdUXI0Wyg?si=ysPQ_7EYl2AkUYx0" />
            </Container>
        </Block_ArticleIntroduction>

        <Block_ArticleOutlined>
            <Sidebar>
                <aside>
                    <Block_TableOfContents />
                </aside>
            </Sidebar>
            <Content>

                <OutlineSection Id="spell-system" LinkName="Spell System">
                    <Block_ArticleHeading>
                        <hgroup>
                            <p>Implementing the</p>
                            <h2>Spell System</h2>
                        </hgroup>
                    </Block_ArticleHeading>

                    <p>The ability system is architected so that each ability instance manages its own state machine. This approach allows for flexible, modular, and extensible ability behaviors, supporting a wide range of gameplay mechanics such as cooldowns, warmups, channeling, and multi-phase effects.</p>

                    <h3>Key Classes</h3>

                    <ul>
                        <li>The abstract <b>base class</b> (<code>Ability</code>) defines the essential interface and properties for all abilities.</li>
                        <li>The basic <b>stateful ability</b> (<code>BasicAbility</code>) contains a basic state machine with passive, warming up, and running down states.</li>
                        <li>The <b>specialised ability</b> (<code>BasicBeamAbility</code>) extends <code>BasicAbility</code> and adds new states to the state machines and logic for applying an effect every few ticks over a period of time.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3>Benefits</h3>

                    <Block_Callout>
                        <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <p><b>Flexibility</b></p>
                            <p>Supports a wide variety of ability types, from instant attacks to complex, multi-phase spells.</p>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </Block_Callout>

                    <Block_Callout>
                        <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <p><b>Maintainability</b></p>
                            <p>Clear state transitions and encapsulation make the system easy to extend and debug.</p>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </Block_Callout>

                    <h3>Drawbacks</h3>

                    <Block_Callout Type="danger">
                        <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <p><b>Ticks are required</b></p>
                            <p>Every ability needs to be processed every frame. If this was an MMO where every player had one hundred abilities, this would require a lot of processing.</p>
                            <p>It would be much more efficient if ability was able to schedule a time for when they next change state and for an invocation to only happen then.</p>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </Block_Callout>
                </OutlineSection>

                <OutlineSection Id="soundtrack" LinkName="Soundtrack">
                    <Block_ArticleHeading>
                        <hgroup>
                            <p>Composing the</p>
                            <h2>Soundtrack</h2>
                        </hgroup>
                    </Block_ArticleHeading>

                    <p>A composed a piece for the background music that's slow and mournful.</p>

                    <figure class="figure-image" style="width: 100%; background: #2727273b;">
                        <picture>
                            <img decoding="async" src="@Assets["media/raidhealersimulator/raidhealersimulator-score.svg"]" alt="The score for 'Sonar' composed for Raid Healer Simulator." loading="lazy" />
                        </picture>
                        <figcaption>The score for 'Sonar' composed for Raid Healer Simulator.</figcaption>
                    </figure>

                    <Block_FigureAudio DefaultVolume="0.125">
                        <TrackName><b>Track 1:</b> Background Music</TrackName>
                        <Description>
                            <p>by Fydar</p>
                        </Description>
                        <AlbumCover>
                            <img decoding="async" src="@Assets["media/raidhealersimulator/card.webp"]" alt="A screenshot from Raid Healer Simulator." loading="lazy" />
                        </AlbumCover>
                        <Sources>
                            <source src="@Assets["media/raidhealersimulator/raidhealersimulator-sonar.ogg"]" type="audio/ogg">
                            <source src="@Assets["media/raidhealersimulator/raidhealersimulator-sonar.mp3"]" type="audio/mpeg">
                        </Sources>
                    </Block_FigureAudio>
                </OutlineSection>

                <OutlineSection Id="user-feedback" LinkName="User Feedback">
                    <Block_ArticleHeading>
                        <hgroup>
                            <p>Analysing the</p>
                            <h2>User Feedback</h2>
                        </hgroup>
                    </Block_ArticleHeading>

                    <p>As a part of Ludum Dare, I submitted my game to the <a href="https://ldjam.com/events/ludum-dare/46/$195962" target="_blank">project Ludum Dare page<SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-external-link" class="external-link-icon" /></a> for feedback. The community was incredibly supportive of the project.</p>

                    <p>Below is a summary of the user feedback left on the project page.</p>

                    <p>Despite some difficulty issues, the game was well-received for its humour, accurate representation of healing, and good use of the theme.</p>

                    <h3>Positives</h3>

                    <Block_Callout>
                        <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <p><b>Accurate representation of healing</b></p>
                            <p>Many players commented that the game accurately captured the experience of healing in an MMO, including the stress, communication with teammates, and difficulty.</p>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </Block_Callout>

                    <Block_Callout>
                        <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <p><b>Great use of the theme</b></p>
                            <p>Players appreciated the intro sequence and chat mechanics that added to the MMO feel.</p>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </Block_Callout>

                    <Block_Callout>
                        <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <p><b>Great game concept</b></p>
                            <p>The core idea of the game was well-received and relatable.</p>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </Block_Callout>

                    <Block_Callout>
                        <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <p><b>Great use of humour</b></p>
                            <p>The chat messages provided humour for many users.</p>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </Block_Callout>

                    <Block_Callout>
                        <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <p><b>Very polished</b></p>
                            <p>Players liked the polished aspects of the game, such as the HUD and chat functionality.</p>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </Block_Callout>

                    <h3>Negatives</h3>

                    <Block_Callout Type="danger">
                        <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <p><b>Extreme difficulty</b></p>
                            <p>The game was considered too difficult by many players, especially for those unfamiliar with MMOs.</p>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </Block_Callout>

                    <Block_Callout Type="danger">
                        <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <p><b>Lack of in-game explanations</b></p>
                            <p>Players found it hard to understand what abilities did due to the lack of tooltips or in-game explanations.</p>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </Block_Callout>

                    <Block_Callout Type="danger">
                        <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
                        <ChildContent>
                            <p><b>Lack of visual feedback</b></p>
                            <p>Some players wished for more visual feedback on the effects of their spells.</p>
                        </ChildContent>
                    </Block_Callout>
                </OutlineSection>

            </Content>
        </Block_ArticleOutlined>
    </div>
</article>
